  "cataloging_subject": {
    "id": "work:aha2749",
    "unit_type": "single_work",
    "label": "The Lanterne of Light",
    "scope_note": "One anonymous Middle English Lollard prose treatise in thirteen numbered chapters, composed after Archbishop Arundel's 1409 Constitutions and attested at John Claydon's 1415 heresy trial. The work is distinct from Harley MSS 2324 and 6613, the reported-lost Claydon copy, the circa-1535 Redman print, Swinburn's 1917 edition, Dean's 1996 partial edition, the U-M encoding, and the repository XML. AHA2749 encodes Swinburn's title page, contents, introduction, complete edited text, appendix, and notes, but omits the printed glossary."
  },
